Package think.rpgitems.data

Class RPGMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<Integer,Object>
        • think.rpgitems.data.RPGMetadata
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Integer,Object>
    public class RPGMetadata
extends HashMap<Integer,Object>
    RPGMetadata is a (bad) way of tagging extra data onto an item without it showing up on the item itself. This uses a similar system to Notch's entity metadata system. The data will be encoded in minecraft colour codes which makes this really inefficient because 1 byte -> 2 bytes(Hex) -> 4 bytes( Colour codes). RPGMetadata is prefixed with CAFE to allow it to be easily detected.
